settings.text: From birth options and preferences to labor prep, postpartum planning, emotional support, and reproductive justice, we cover it all. With virtual consultations and virtual birth doulas, you can access personalized care and support from the comfort of your own home.

We are here to provide you with expert care, guidance, and emotional support throughout your labor and birth process. Our doulas will work closely with you and your birth team to create a birth plan that aligns with your unique needs and desires.

Your birth options & preferences

Your doula will listen attentively to your birth preferences and provide guidance and support in understanding your options, including topics such as natural birth, medicated birth, cesarean birth, and more.

Birth plan development

Your doula can help you develop a personalized birth plan that aligns with your preferences and values, providing valuable insights and recommendations based on their expertise.

Comfort measures during labor

Your doula can provide information and guidance on various comfort measures during labor, including birthing ball & peanut ball exercises, breathing techniques, relaxation techniques, movement, and positioning, to help you cope with the physical and emotional aspects of labor.

Postpartum planning

Your doula can discuss postpartum planning, including topics such as breastfeeding, newborn care, emotional well-being, and self-care, to ensure you are prepared for the postpartum period.

Emotional support

Your doula recognizes the emotional aspects of pregnancy, childbirth, and postpartum, and can provide compassionate support and guidance in navigating any fears, anxieties, or concerns you may have.

Birth options and interventions

Your doula can provide information on different birth options and interventions that may arise during childbirth, including risks, benefits, and alternatives, to help you make informed decisions.

Reproductive justice

As an advocate for reproductive justice, doulas may discuss topics related to social justice, equity, and inclusivity in childbirth, and how it impacts your birthing experience.

We will plan and discuss important topics before your estimated due date.

During these visits, we'll

  • Build our connection
  • Discuss your birth preferences
  • Create a Birth Plan
  • Practice relaxation techniques in our Labor Prep class
  • Talk about comfort measures and labor positions
  • Provide tips on laboring at home

These visits are designed to help you get ready for your baby, address any questions or concerns you may have, and ensure you feel prepared and confident for your upcoming birth experience.

Wondering what we'll cover? Check out our Planning Checklist filled with topics we can explore together.

Your experienced doula will be by your side throughout your labor, providing continuous support, encouragement, and comfort, regardless of your chosen birth location (home, birthing center, or hospital). Our services include:

  • Rebozo Massage: Utilizing the traditional Mexican technique of using a shawl-like cloth, your doula will provide gentle and soothing movements to help ease tension and promote relaxation during labor.
  • Birthing Ball: Your doula will assist you in using a birthing ball, a large inflatable ball, as a tool for comfort, support, and optimal positioning during labor.
  • Breathing Techniques: Your doula will guide you through various breathing techniques to help you stay relaxed, focused, and manage pain during labor.
  • Complimentary Birth Photography and Video: As a special gift to you, your doula will capture precious moments of your labor and birth through photography and video, which will be provided to you on a flash drive to treasure for a lifetime.
  • Birth Room Ambiance: Your doula will create a calming and soothing environment in your birth room with a Himalayan salt lamp, essential oil diffuser, blood orange mist, and arnica massage oil to promote relaxation and comfort during labor.

With our comprehensive support through labor, you can feel confident and empowered during this transformative experience.

Our postpartum doula services extend beyond the birth, providing essential support during the early weeks of parenthood. We offer:

  • In-Home Visits: Within the first two weeks postpartum, your doula will schedule visits to your home, providing emotional support, practical assistance, and answering any questions you may have about the birth experience or newborn care.
  • Emotional Support: Your doula is here to listen and provide a safe space for you to share your feelings, emotions, and thoughts about adjusting to life with a new baby, whether it's the good, the bad, or the tough stuff.
  • Resources and Tips on Infant Feeding: Your doula will provide valuable resources and tips on infant feeding, including breastfeeding, bottle-feeding, and introducing solids, to help you navigate this important aspect of newborn care.
  • Meal Planning and Grocery Lists: Your doula will help you plan meals and provide a grocery list to make your life a little easier during the postpartum period. We can also arrange contact-free drop-off of needed items through community support, a meal train, or assistance from friends and family.
  • Ongoing Postpartum Care: Your doula understands that postpartum care extends beyond the initial weeks with a newborn. We are committed to providing ongoing support to new parents, those with toddlers, or multiple children through simple acts of caring for the parent, while you care for your family.

Your postpartum visits are designed to meet you where you're at, from the comfort of your home, and provide comprehensive support to help you navigate the early weeks of parenthood with confidence and ease.
I offer 24/7 scheduled support at the rate of $100/hour for the following services

settings.title: Overnight Doula
settings.text:
The most shared fear among new parents are the sleepless nights. It’s true, new babies can be night owls, but with the extra support of an overnight doula it can be the best bonding experience with your new baby.

Call me, text or video chat for help and encouragement with nighttime bottle feedings, initial lactation education, questions about pumping and milk storage—anything to help you and your baby find your rhythm.

settings.title: Adoption & Surrogacy
settings.text:
Are you building your family, but aren’t sure where to find the right resources? Deciding to adopt or have a surrogate carrier are both dig decisions. You deserve to walk into parenthood feeling empowered and ready.

We will have consultations to answer your questions and I can provide local resources such as milk donors, parent support groups, and suggest LGBTQIA+ providers. We can talk about your legal rights as parents. I provide birth support for surrogate carriers in addition to the intended parents.

settings.title: Miscarriage & Bereavement
settings.text:
Going through such a difficult time, that is often suffered alone and in silence, I walk with and support your family through the loss of your baby.

If that loss is through miscarriage, stillbirth, or a diagnosis that means the baby will not live long after being delivered, with gentle encouragement, we say hello and goodbye to your little one, honor their life, and I remain available for grief counseling thereafter via phone and video calls, texts, and email.
We believe strongly that everyone deserves a doula. No one will be turned away for lack of resources. Reach out and we can discuss how we can best support you best.
